nce a time when no one was playing a rogue and they were actually needed ;p. Well now it seems that almost everyone has a rogue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ueqjetx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQ JetX</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://eqscreenshot.homestead.com/files/icon57.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/23/02 3:07:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utropicsdelight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TropicsDelight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 610<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 4:30:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2202.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So why did you pick your class?</span><hr size=1> I picked a SK because I love fear kiting things and love the idea of a creature running in terror from a SK as he mauls it from behind. I had played a necromancer before this and he was too situational and almost too easy really. The pet was a blender and the dots and hp/mana spells made playing him a breeze. I needed more of a challenge and SK is right up near the top of tough to play classes (not that Verant made any class really tough, bard is the worst and still a moron can manage to get by).<br><br>I am a little disheartened about how the SK class ends up. Without a huge damage 2 hander they do next to no damage at all in a battle and are one of the most useless classes in a raid unless they get to pull. For all the fear a Shadowknight should invoke in his enemies a mob in EQ must be alot more terrified by Rangers and their 1500  attack, duel wielding, attack. Shadowknights are about as scary as a miniature bunny in comparison to the other classes of EQ. <p>Tropics Delight Shadowknight of the Greenmist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukerai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1221<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 4:35:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2202.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So why did you pick your class?</span><hr size=1> I always like being a Necromancer and so I play one in damn near every game I play. I started my necro on Innoruuk but when Vaz opened. Me and my friends moved here. I decided to change classes and therefore made a Ranger, cause I heard they were fun to play. I got to 27 but finding a group was a royal pain in the ass. Therefore I dropped that and started up a Cleric. Was a cleric til lvl 46 but it got the point the day to day lvling of a cleric bored the fuck out of me. So I transfered over my necro and haven been on that ever since. I am currently making an SK twink cause I wanted a melee. Every1 and their dog has a monk, my friend is a rogue and I had a ranger. So my options narrowed down to warrior, paly, SK. I played a warrior once, didn't really enjoy it and being good is no fun, so SK it is. <p>Kerai Cookies<br>-------------------------<br>Welcome to Necroland, would you like some mana with that?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=celeahleshok>Celeah Leshok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 4:42:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecom