p align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So why did you pick your class?</span><hr size=1> I thought it was kew to make a rogue called 'Stabs' 'Steals' or 'sneekz' <p>Assassin of Vazaelle<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53125" target="main">Kuldiin's Profile </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uzixx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zixx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 9:10:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2202.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So why did you pick your class?</span><hr size=1> <br>I played a few classes when I first got EQ. Tried to find a server with friends on it, but they kept moving. Unfortunately, I didn't realize how the attribute points worked and my first shaman on Prexus I think I maxed his strength so I wouldn't have to run to town as often(cuz of weight)  <br><br>/sigh<br><br>Finally figured it out and made a shaman with the right starting attributes. But after messing around with a warrior and ranger, I wanted a char that could heal himself, bind wherever I wanted to go and have sow. And for some reason I really enjoy shaman class, least there's always something to do on a raid.<br><br>Zixx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ufiido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fiido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 9:15:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2202.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top a